# =============================================================================
# Build-context exclusions for backend/Dockerfile
# =============================================================================
# Everything NOT listed here is uploaded to the docker daemon and can end up in
# an image layer. Two reasons this file matters:
#   1. SECRECY — a layer is permanently readable by anyone with the image, even
#      if a later layer deletes the file. `.env` must never get in.
#   2. CORRECTNESS — host artifacts (node_modules compiled for Windows, a stale
#      generated Prisma client) would overwrite what the build produced for Alpine.
#
# Anything the running app needs MUST stay out of this file. In particular:
#   - prisma/    (schemas — the image generates the clients from them)
#   - docs/      (openapi.yaml — hand-written, served by src/utils/swagger.js)
# =============================================================================

# --- Secrets: never in a layer -----------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key

# --- Host build artifacts ----------------------------------------------------
# node_modules: compiled for the host OS/ABI. The image runs `npm ci` on Alpine;
# copying these in would ship native addons (bcrypt) built for the wrong libc.
node_modules/
# src/generated: the image regenerates the Prisma clients for its own platform.
# A host-generated client carries the wrong query-engine binary target.
src/generated/
dist/
build/
coverage/
.nyc_output
.npm
.node_repl_history
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# --- Runtime scratch ---------------------------------------------------------
# Local log output. Note this pattern only matches *.log — logs/logger.js itself
# MUST reach the image (app.js imports it).
logs/*.log
# Multer's upload staging area. The directory is recreated by the Dockerfile;
# stale uploads shouldn't be baked in.
public/temp/*
!public/temp/.gitkeep

# --- Version control ---------------------------------------------------------
# .git is often the largest thing in the context and leaks full history.
.git/
.gitignore
.svn/
.hg/

# --- Editors / OS --------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Tooling not needed at runtime --------------------------------------------
Dockerfile*
.dockerignore
docker-compose*.yml
docker-compose*.yaml
.prettierrc
.prettierignore
.agents/
skills-lock.json
